  "prompt": "How does Flipkart make profits?",
  "response": "Flipkart makes profits through several key revenue streams:\n\n1. Product Sales\n- Selling products directly to consumers at marked-up prices\n- Commission from third-party sellers on their platform\n- Wide range of product categories with different profit margins\n\n2. Marketplace Model\n- Charging sellers a commission on each sale\n- Providing logistics and warehousing services for a fee\n- Taking a percentage of transaction value\n\n3. Advertising Revenue\n- Selling advertising space on their platform\n- Sponsored product listings\n- Promotional opportunities for brands\n\n4. Logistics Services\n- Offering shipping and delivery services to sellers\n- Charging for warehousing and fulfillment\n- Efficient supply chain management\n\n5. Digital Wallet and Financial Services\n- Flipkart Pay Later\n- Cashback and rewards programs\n- Processing transaction fees\n\n6. Strategic Partnerships\n- Collaborations with brands\n- Joint promotional activities\n- Cross-platform marketing\n\n7. Subsidiary Services\n- PhonePe (digital payment platform)\n- Myntra (fashion e-commerce)\n\n8. Data Monetization\n- Selling consumer insights and trends\n- Targeted marketing opportunities\n\nThese diverse revenue streams help Flipkart generate profits and maintain a competitive edge in the Indian e-commerce market.",
